docker --version
This is used to check version

sudo docker pull ubuntu 

Used to pull container/docker images from docker hub

sudo docker images 
For checking docker images

sudo docker run (image name)
To a specific image 
sudo docker run -it -d  
It runs container
-it = interactive terminal 
-d = daemon (runs in the background)
sudo docker ps
shows container in running state
sudo docker ps -a 
Shows running and stop state containers to give all existing containers.
 sudo docker stop (container id)
 
 To stop container from running
 sudo docker exec -it (container id)
 
 sudo apt-get 
 To update containers
 
 exit
 To get out of the container system
 sudo docker kill (container id) :To kill/terminate running container .It complete terrmination different from stop
 sudo docker rmi (container id):sudo docker rmi (container id):to remove container from system 
 
 
